The airline says COVID-19 regulations announced this week for crews are impractical. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Emirates has cancelled flights to Durban. The airline says COVID-19 regulations announced this week for crews are impractical. READ: SA Lockdown: Strict international travel rules announced Economic Development, Tourism and Environmental Affairs MEC, Nomusa Dube-Ncube is working with the national government to deal with the issue. eNCA's Anlie Hattingh spoke to Carla da Silva, chairperson at the Board of Airline Representatives of South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 Meanwhile, according to the Board of Airline Representatives of SA (BARSA), new government regulations for aircrews aren't what was discussed during consultations. "We escalated it to be resolved. We were consulted and were very happy with the department of transport in the sense that they consulted with the industry. We were content. Unfortunately, this issue arose thereafter", said BARSA Chairperson Carla da Silva. As of 1 October, international travel for leisure and business is allowed, while leisure visitors from countries deemed high-risk will not be allowed into South Africa. Watch the videos above for more on this story.